enum cvmx_pip_port_parse_mode_t

Enumeration representing the amount of packet processing and validation performed by the input hardware.

Enumerator:
CVMX_PIP_PORT_CFG_MODE_NONE 

Packet input doesn't perform any processing of the input packet.

CVMX_PIP_PORT_CFG_MODE_SKIPL2 

Full packet processing is performed with pointer starting at the L2 (ethernet MAC) header.

CVMX_PIP_PORT_CFG_MODE_SKIPIP 

Input packets are assumed to be IP.

Results from non IP packets is undefined. Pointers reference the beginning of the IP header.

enum cvmx_pip_qos_watch_types

This enumeration controls how a QoS watcher matches a packet.

Deprecated:
This enumeration was used with cvmx_pip_config_watcher which has been deprecated.
Enumerator:
CVMX_PIP_QOS_WATCH_DISABLE 

QoS watcher is diabled.

CVMX_PIP_QOS_WATCH_PROTNH 

QoS watcher will match based on the IP protocol.

CVMX_PIP_QOS_WATCH_TCP 

QoS watcher will match TCP packets to a specific destination port.

CVMX_PIP_QOS_WATCH_UDP 

QoS watcher will match UDP packets to a specific destination port.

enum cvmx_pip_tag_mode_t

This enumeration is used in PIP tag config to control how POW tags are generated by the hardware.

Enumerator:
CVMX_PIP_TAG_MODE_TUPLE 

Always use tuple tag algorithm.

This is the only mode supported on Pass 1

CVMX_PIP_TAG_MODE_MASK 

Always use mask tag algorithm.

CVMX_PIP_TAG_MODE_IP_OR_MASK 

If packet is IP, use tuple else use mask.

CVMX_PIP_TAG_MODE_TUPLE_XOR_MASK 

tuple XOR mask

enum cvmx_pow_tag_type_t

Tag type definitions.

Enumerator:
CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_ORDERED 

Tag ordering is maintained.

CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_ATOMIC 

Tag ordering is maintained, and at most one PP has the tag.

CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_NULL 

The work queue entry from the order

  • NEVER tag switch from NULL to NULL.
CVMX_POW_TAG_TYPE_NULL_NULL 

A tag switch to NULL, and there is no space reserved in POW

  • NEVER tag switch to NULL_NULL
  • NEVER tag switch from NULL_NULL
  • NULL_NULL is entered at the beginning of time and on a deschedule.
  • NULL_NULL can be exited by a new work request. A NULL_SWITCH load can also switch the state to NULL
enum cvmx_uart_bits_t

LCR bits 0 and 1 control the number of bits per character.

See the following table for encodings:

  • 00 = 5 bits (bits 0-4 sent)
  • 01 = 6 bits (bits 0-5 sent)
  • 10 = 7 bits (bits 0-6 sent)
  • 11 = 8 bits (all bits sent)
